reference: Lactational Amenorrhea Method. LAM is a temporary family planning method that helps to delay return of fertility after having a baby. For this method to be effective,  Your baby must be exclusively breastfed. LAM requires 3 conditions and all must be met. 1. Your menstruation has not returned after giving birth.  2.  The baby is exclusively breastfed and is fed frequently. 3. The baby is less than six months old.
